&gt; Is there a good reason for no-nameserver tolerance?  Am I missing an
&gt; important (and surely DoD-bureaucratic) justification for this
&gt; foolishness?

One unfortunate reason is that there are still vendors that don't
provide domain resolvers.  One example that affects us is ACC with
ACCES/MVS.  They've been promising a resolver for years, but still
have not delivered.

